o help the child understand transitions and expectations, reducing impulsivity.  \n\n**Approach:**  \nImplement **Behavioral Coaching** to reinforce positive behaviors and improve self-regulation.\n\n**Tools:**  \n- [NIH - Managing Hyperactive Behavior](https://www.nih.gov)\n- [APA - Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder](https://www.apa.org)\n\n### **Conduct Problems**\n**Steps:**  \n1. Set clear expectations and consistent consequences for behavior to promote accountability.\n2. Engage in role-playing scenarios to practice appropriate social interactions and conflict resolution skills.  \n\n**Approach:**  \nApply **Parent-Child Interaction Therapy (PCIT)** to enhance parent-child relationships and improve behavioral outcomes.\n\n**Tools:**  \n- [CDC - Conduct Disorders](https://www.cdc.gov)\n- [Mayo Clinic - Parenting Strategies](https://www.mayoclinic.org)\n\n---\n\n##SECTION: Monitor\n- **Daily:** Encourage the child to share one positive emotion and one challenging emotion they experienced each day.\n- **Weekly:** Hold a family meeting to discuss successes and areas for growth, fostering open communication.\n- **Alert:** If the child exhibits extreme emotional outbursts or engages in harmful behaviors, it may be time to seek professional help.\n\n---\n\n##SECTION: Support\n- **Who:** Consider consulting a pediatric therapist, school psychologist, or behavioral coach for specialized support.\n- **Crisis:** In case of emergencies, contact 911 or the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline at 988.\n- **Urgency:** Given the very high risk in emotional regulation and hyperactivity, timely intervention is essential for effective support.	AI Generated	3	f	2025-10-29 16:24:44.673	2025-10-29 16:24:44.673
